# Yetti Design System Standards

## Component Usage Standards

### Button Component

**ALWAYS use the Button component for all interactive elements:**

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT - Use Button component
import Button from "@/components/ui/Button";

<Button href="/contact" size="md">Get Started</Button>
<Button variant="outline" size="md">Learn More</Button>
<Button size="sm">Small Action</Button>

// ❌ WRONG - Don't create custom buttons
<button className="px-4 py-2 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded">Click me</button>
<a className="px-6 py-3 bg-gradient-to-r from-[#6086f7] to-[#4c6ef5]">Link</a>
```

**Button Variants:**

- `primary`: Gradient blue buttons (main CTAs) - Uses #6086f7 to #4c6ef5
- `secondary`: Light gray gradient (secondary actions)
- `outline`: Bordered buttons (tertiary actions)
- `ghost`: Text-only buttons (subtle actions)

**Button Sizes:**

- `sm`: Small buttons (px-4 py-2)
- `md`: Medium buttons (px-6 py-3) - DEFAULT
- `lg`: Large buttons (px-8 py-4) - Use sparingly for hero CTAs only

### Card Component

**ALWAYS use Card components for content containers:**

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT - Use Card component
import { Card, CardContent, CardHeader } from "@/components/ui/Card";

<Card>
  <CardHeader>Title</CardHeader>
  <CardContent>Content here</CardContent>
</Card>

// ❌ WRONG - Don't create custom cards
<div className="bg-white rounded-2xl p-6 shadow-sm">Content</div>
```

## Color Standards

### Primary Colors

**ALWAYS use these exact color values:**

```css
/* Primary Blue Gradient */
bg-gradient-to-r from-[#6086f7] to-[#4c6ef5]

/* Text Colors */
text-[#6086f7]   /* Primary text */
text-[#4c6ef5]   /* Secondary text */
text-gray-600    /* Muted text */
text-gray-900    /* Dark text */

/* Background Colors */
bg-blue-50       /* Light blue backgrounds */
bg-gray-50       /* Light gray backgrounds */
bg-white         /* White backgrounds */
```

### Color Usage Rules

- **Primary CTAs**: Always use `from-[#6086f7] to-[#4c6ef5]` gradient
- **Text links**: Use `text-[#6086f7]` with `hover:text-[#4c6ef5]`
- **Borders**: Use `border-gray-100` for subtle, `border-gray-200` for defined
- **Backgrounds**: Use `bg-gray-50` for sections, `bg-white` for cards

## Spacing Standards

### Padding & Margins

**ALWAYS use these spacing values:**

```css
/* Section Padding */
py-24           /* Large sections */
py-16           /* Medium sections */
py-12           /* Small sections */

/* Container Padding */
px-6            /* Mobile padding */
px-8            /* Desktop padding */
px-12           /* Large desktop padding */

/* Component Spacing */
p-6             /* Card padding */
p-8             /* Large card padding */
gap-8           /* Grid gaps */
gap-6           /* Small gaps */
gap-4           /* Button gaps */
```

### Container Widths

```css
max-w-6xl       /* Main content containers */
max-w-4xl       /* Narrow content */
max-w-3xl       /* Text content */
max-w-7xl       /* Full-width sections */
```

## Border Radius Standards

**ALWAYS use these border radius values:**

```css
rounded-lg      /* Small elements (buttons sm) */
rounded-xl      /* Medium elements (buttons md) - DEFAULT */
rounded-2xl     /* Large elements (cards, containers) */
rounded-full    /* Pills, badges, avatars */
```

## Typography Standards

### Font Sizes

```css
text-xs         /* Small labels, badges */
text-sm         /* Small text, captions */
text-base       /* Body text */
text-lg         /* Large body text */
text-xl         /* Small headings */
text-2xl        /* Medium headings */
text-3xl        /* Large headings */
text-4xl        /* Extra large headings */
text-5xl        /* Hero headings */
text-7xl        /* Massive headings */
text-8xl        /* Giant headings */
```

### Font Family

- **Rule:** Use "Roboto" as the primary sans-serif font, with system fallbacks.
- **Rationale:** Modern, readable, and consistent brand font with excellent web performance.
- **Headings:** All h1-h6 elements use Roboto with font-weight: 700 (bold) for strong visual hierarchy.

### Font Weights

```css
font-light      /* Hero headings */
font-medium     /* Subheadings, buttons */
font-semibold   /* Important text */
font-bold       /* Emphasis */
font-[700]      /* All headings (h1-h6) - automatically applied */
```

## Animation Standards

### Transitions

**ALWAYS use these transition classes:**

```css
transition-all duration-300    /* Standard transitions */
hover:-translate-y-1           /* Card hover lift */
hover:-translate-y-0.5         /* Button hover lift */
group-hover:scale-105         /* Image hover scale */
group-hover:translate-x-1     /* Arrow animations */
```

### Hover Effects

```css
hover:shadow-lg               /* Card shadows */
hover:shadow-md               /* Button shadows */
hover:opacity-80              /* Link opacity */
group-hover:opacity-100       /* Reveal effects */
```

## Layout Standards

### Grid Systems

```css
grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3    /* Responsive grids */
grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2                   /* Two-column layouts */
gap-8                                         /* Standard grid gap */
```

### Flexbox

```css
flex items-center justify-center              /* Centered content */
flex flex-col sm:flex-row                     /* Responsive flex */
gap-4                                         /* Standard flex gap */
```

## Component Patterns

### Section Headers

**ALWAYS use this pattern for section headers:**

```tsx
<div className="text-center mb-16">
  <span className="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-gray-200 bg-white px-4 py-1 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.28em] text-gray-600 mb-6">
    Section Badge
  </span>
  <h2 className="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-light text-black mb-6">
    Section Title
  </h2>
  <p className="text-lg text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto">Section description</p>
</div>
```

### Link Patterns

**ALWAYS use this pattern for links with arrows:**

```tsx
<Link
  href="/path"
  className="inline-flex items-center text-[#6086f7] font-medium hover:text-[#4c6ef5] transition-colors duration-200 group/link"
>
  Link Text
  <svg
    className="ml-2 w-4 h-4 transition-transform group-hover/link:translate-x-1"
    fill="none"
    stroke="currentColor"
    viewBox="0 0 24 24"
  >
    <path
      strokeLinecap="round"
      strokeLinejoin="round"
      strokeWidth={2}
      d="M17 8l4 4m0 0l-4 4m4-4H3"
    />
  </svg>
</Link>
```

## Forbidden Patterns

### ❌ NEVER DO THESE:

- Create custom buttons instead of using Button component
- Use `size="lg"` buttons unless absolutely necessary (hero CTAs only)
- Use arbitrary color values (use only defined colors)
- Use arbitrary spacing values (use only defined spacing)
- Create custom cards instead of using Card component
- Use different border radius values
- Skip hover effects on interactive elements
- Use different animation durations
- Create inconsistent section headers

### ✅ ALWAYS DO THESE:

- Use Button component for all interactive elements
- Use `size="md"` as the default button size
- Use Card component for content containers
- Follow the exact color palette
- Use consistent spacing values
- Apply hover effects to interactive elements
- Use the standard section header pattern
- Follow the established animation patterns

## Implementation Checklist

Before adding any new component or page:

1. ✅ Does it use Button component for interactive elements?
2. ✅ Does it use Card component for content containers?
3. ✅ Does it follow the color standards?
4. ✅ Does it use consistent spacing?
5. ✅ Does it have proper hover effects?
6. ✅ Does it follow the typography standards?
7. ✅ Does it use the correct border radius?
8. ✅ Does it follow the section header pattern?

**Remember: Consistency is key. Every component should feel like part of the same design system.**
